    "summary": "After graduating from University in 1977 I worked in:\n\u2022 The educational sector in the Netherlands and Zimbabwe(secondant schools, polytechnics and post graduate programmes) for about 20 years \n\u2022 Development cooperation: From 1998 I was team and programme manager for the International Institute for Communication and Development (IICD, www.iicd.org) and as such actively involved in ICT4D (ICT for development ) projects. \n\u2022 Development cooperation: Since 2011 I am involved as lecturer at the Virtual University of Uganda (VUU; www.virtualuni.ac.ug). The VUU (4 accredited MsC programmes; 100% distance education) is a private initiative aiming at making academic education available to the rural population in East-Africa. I am lecturing in the programme Public Health and ICT4D (see ww.virtualuni.ac.ug/programmes).\n\u2022 Private sector the Netherlands: From December 2007 -2009 I worked as senior advisor/ programme manager at HEC (see www.hec.nl)\n\u2022  Academics: Vrije Universiteit (www.vu.nl/en), From 2009 until 2012 I worked as Senior Information manager for the Technical Faculties of the University, \n\u2022 Public sector: From 2013 until 2018 I worked as strategic information advisor for the municipality of Amsterdam in the Cate sector\n\u2022 Care sector:  From the the the midst of 2017 I worked as a researcher for Garage2020, an innovation hub in the youthcare (parttime in the beginning)\n\nI am a strategic thinker with a strong analytical capacity. Result oriented, diplomatic and a well appreciated team and programme manager.\n",
